---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import Prose from '../components/Prose.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The terms that govern your use of Pinkflow services, including Namescape."
  lastUpdated={site.lastUpdated.terms}
>
  <Prose>
    <p>These Terms were last updated on {site.lastUpdated.terms}.</p>

    <h2>1. Agreement to these Terms</h2>
    <p>
      By creating an account or using any Pinkflow service, you agree to these Terms.
      If you do not agree, do not use the service.
    </p>

    <h2>2. About Pinkflow</h2>
    <p>
      {site.operatorLine}. These Terms apply to all Pinkflow services,
      currently including <a href={site.products[0].url!}>Namescape</a>. Future services we
      release are also covered automatically.
    </p>

    <h2>3. What Namescape does</h2>
    <p>
      Namescape takes a short description of an idea and returns a shortlist of domain names
      with price guidance, likely-availability clues, and registrar checkout paths. Suggestions
      are guidance to help you shortlist names before checkout &mdash; not a final answer.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Your account</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You must be at least 16 years old to create an account.</li>
      <li>Provide accurate information and keep it current.</li>
      <li>One account per person.</li>
      <li>You are responsible for keeping your credentials safe.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Search packs and billing</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Namescape is paid for with one-time search packs, priced in USD. See <a href="/pricing">Pricing</a>.</li>
      <li>Payment is processed by Paddle, the {site.paddle.role.toLowerCase()}. Your card statement will show <strong>{site.paddle.statementLabel}</strong>.</li>
      <li>Search packs are <strong>consumed when a search is run</strong>.</li>
      <li>Packs are <strong>non-transferable</strong>, have <strong>no cash value</strong>, and cannot be resold.</li>
      <li>Packs are a <strong>one-time purchase</strong>. No subscription, no auto-renewal.</li>
      <li>Purchases are generally final once delivered or used. See <a href="/refunds">Refund Policy</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Using the service responsibly</h2>
    <p>You will not:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Scrape or bulk-harvest suggestions for redistribution.</li>
      <li>Resell suggestions or access to the service in bulk.</li>
      <li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract internal models or sources.</li>
      <li>Use the service for trademark infringement, cybersquatting, or other illegal activity.</li>
      <li>Run high-volume automated queries that bypass normal use.</li>
      <li>Share account credentials or access tokens with third parties.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Your inputs</h2>
    <p>
      You own the prompts and inputs you submit. You grant Pinkflow a limited permission to
      process those inputs solely to deliver the service to you.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Our outputs</h2>
    <p>
      Suggestions and availability data are <strong>guidance, not guarantees</strong>. You must
      independently verify domain availability, registrar pricing, and trademark or other legal
      clearance with the relevant registrar and authorities before buying or using any name.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Service changes and availability</h2>
    <p>
      We do not guarantee uninterrupted access. Features may change, be added, or be removed.
      We may also restrict or suspend access for maintenance, security, or policy violations.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Disclaimers</h2>
    <p>
      The service is provided "as is" and "as available". We do not guarantee that suggestions,
      availability clues, or price guidance are accurate, complete, or current.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, Pinkflow and its operator are not liable for any
      indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the service.
      Our total aggregate liability for any claim is limited to the amount you paid us in the
      12 months preceding the claim. This does not affect any non-waivable consumer rights you
      may have under applicable law.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Indemnification</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, you agree to indemnify Pinkflow and its operator
      against claims arising from your misuse of the service or your violation of these Terms
      or applicable law.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Termination</h2>
    <p>
      You can delete your account at any time. We may suspend or terminate access for violations
      of these Terms, with notice where reasonable.
    </p>

    <h2>14. Changes to these Terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these Terms from time to time. We will revise the "Last updated" date above
      and, for material changes, notify you by email or in-app. Continued use after a change
      means you accept the updated Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>15. Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms are governed by the laws of {site.jurisdiction}, without regard to conflict
      of law principles.
    </p>

    <h2>16. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these Terms? Reach us at <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>
      or via the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
    </p>
  </Prose>
</LegalLayout>
